						               													<description>Catch a Dragon by the Tail is a super-simple free print and play game. It's press-your-luck dice game for two to four players with a &amp;quot;hatching dragons&amp;quot; fantasy theme.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;At the start of your turn you roll four custom six-sided dice (or standard dice that you cross-reference with a table), then choose to gather identical dice or different dice. After you do, you can stop rolling and score or you can roll the dice you haven't collected.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Homogenous sets of dice score the best: two dice score four points, three score nine, four score 16. Consecutive dice score second-best, with a run of two scoring four, three scoring six, and four scoring eight. &amp;quot;Loner&amp;quot; dice score one point each.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If you choose to roll again, what you roll may make you end your turn and score nothing.&amp;#10;&amp;bull; If you're collecting identical dice and you don't get at least one result that matches what you're collecting, your turn ends and you score nothing.&amp;#10;&amp;bull; If you're collecting different dice and at least one result matches a die you already have, your turn ends and you score nothing.&amp;#10;...Otherwise, you may collect one or more valid dice and choose to stop and score or roll the un-collected dice yet again.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game ends after four rounds. The highest score wins. Break ties with an additional round of play.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;-description from designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
